Name: Cold Cut-out
Help: Desired cut-out temperature in coldest position/ set-point

Name: Warm Cut-out
Help: Desired cut-out temperature in warmest position/ set-point

Name: Default Temp Set
Help: In case of knob (potentiometer) failure, this setting would bring the temperature set-point to a particular desired position, between the warmest and coldest set-points, which could be set as the percentage between warmest (0%) and coldest(100%) positions/ set-points

Name: Cold Differential
Help: Difference in the cut-in and cut-out temperartures at the coldest position (set-point)

Name: Warm Differential
Help: Difference in the cut-in and cut-out temperartures at the warmest position (set-point)

Name: Fan stops on compressor cutout
Help: If this pamater is enabled , the Fan will stop when the compressor stops.

Name: Min Runtime
Help: To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-outs, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor runs for atleast the specified time. This parameter overrides the cut-out temperature.

Name: Max Runtime function
Help: Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary deep temperatures."

Name: Max Stoptime Function
Help:
"To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-ins, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor remains in idle state for atleast the specified time. This parameter overrides the cut-in temperatures.

Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary warm temperatures.

Name: Max Runtime
Help: Enable or disable option for Max Run time."

Name: Max Stoptime
Help: Enable or disable option for Max Stop time.

Name: Error RunTime
Help: To avoid compressor damage due to continuous running for long durations, this parameter would set maximum run time allowed for the compressor.

Name: Error StopTime
Help: To avoid long idle state of compressor, this parameter would set maximum stop time allowed, after which the compressor would start irrespective of cut-in temperature.

Name: Alarm low function
Help: This parameter only becomes active in the unlikely event of temperature sensor failure, the compressor would run for specified fixed run time, to maintain safe temprature of the application.

Name: Alarm high function
Help: This parameter only becomes active in the unlikely event of temperature sensor failure, the compressor would stop for specified fixed stop time, to maintain safe temprature of the application.

Name: Alarm on Heater relay
Help: Enable or disable option for Alarm undertemp Function.

Name: Alarm on Fan relay
Help: Enable or disable option for Alarm overtemp Function.

Name: Alarm on Relay Inverted
Help: Heater-relay will be used for alarm-output if this parameter is enabled.

Name: Cold Overtemp Alarm
Help: Fan-relay will be used for alarm-output if this parameter is enabled.

Name: Warm Overtemp Alarm
Help: When this function is enabled , the alarm relay contact will be open at alarm and closed under normal operation.

Name: Cold Undertemp Alarm
Help: Warmest temperature allowed at the coldest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Warm Undertemp Alarm
Help: Warmest temperature allowed at the warmest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Alarm Delay
Help: Coldest temperature allowed at the coldest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Defrost Method (name)
Enum: 0:No defrost,1:Start;Time Stop;Control temp,2:Start;Time Stop;Defrost temp,3:Start & Stop;Defrost temp
Help: Coldest temperature allowed at the warmest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Fan on during defrost
Help: Time delay to raise over or undertemperature alarm signal. It is not active at power up.

Name: Hot-Gas Defrost
Help: Selection of defrost method

Name: Defrost Terminate Temperature
Help: 1. No Defrost: Select this option if you don't need defrost functionality. If this option is selected, it will disable all defrost related parameters.

Name: Defrost Start Temperature
Help: 2. Start by Time, Stop by Cabinet temperature: Select this option, if you want to start defrost after fixed specified accumulated compressor run time intervals, and stop the defrost when the desired Cabinet temperature (measures by temperature/ cabinet sensor) is reached as set in the Defrost Terminate temperatur (DTT) parameter.

Name: Minimum Defrost Time
Help: 3. Start by Time, Stop by Evaporator temperature: Select this option, if you want to start defrost after fixed specified accumulated compressor run time intervals, and stop the defrost when the desired evaporator temperature (measures by evaporator sensor) is reached as set in the Defrost Terminate temperatur (DTT) parameter.

Name: Minimum Defrost Interval
Help: 4. Start and Stop by Evaporator temperature: Select this option, if you want to start and stop the defrost based on evaporator temperature.

Name: Fan Start Delay After Defrost
Help: Used in natural defrost method to accelerate the defrosting.

Name: Fan Start Delay
Help: if set: The compressor will contine to run during defrost. The relay-output is used to control a Hot Gas By-pass valve instead of the defrost heater.

Name: Fan Stop Delay
Help: Temperature at which the defrost session will be terminated.

Name: Voltage Protect function
Help: If the evaporator temperature is above the defrost Reset Temperature, the defrost interval counter will be reset to zero at this temperature.

Name: Voltage Threshold
Help: TIP: This temperature should be set lower than the Defrost Terminate Temperature. The purpose of this function is to only count the time, where the evaporator is cold enough to build up frost.""

Name: Maximum Cut-in Voltage
Help: Evaporator Temperature at which the defrost can be triggered if option 4 (Start and Stop by Evaporator temperature sensor) is selected

Name: Stop function
Help: If a heater is used to run the defrost session, this is the delay for compressor start after defrost terminates (waiting for water to drip off the evaporator)

Name: Zero-Cross switching Function
Help: Minimum time limit defined for defrost duration

Name: Sensor Type (name)
Help: Maximum time limit defined for defrost duration

Name: Zero-Cross Switching
Help: Minimum time interval between two defrost sessions

Name: Remote display fahrenheit
Help: Maximum time interval between two defrost sessions. Only used by defrost method 4 (Start and Stop by Evaporator temperature)

Name: Remote display 1 decimal
Help: This fan delay is to avoid circulating warm air from evaporator due to defrost seesion.

Name: Remote Lock at Defrost
Help: Time delay to start the fan after compressor cut-in

Name: Remote Indicate Defrost
Help: Time delay to stop the fan afer compressor cut-out

Name: Remote Stop Function
Help: The lowest voltage at which the compressor is allowed to Cut-in.

Name: Remote Sensor Offset
Help: When voltage falls below the Minimum cut-in voltage, it waits until it reaches (MIV-VTR) after which it cuts-out the compressor. After this, the compressor would start again at Minimum Cut-in voltage (MIV) parameter.

Name: Remote Sensor Deviation
Help: This parameter will avoid sudden switching on and off of compressor due to voltage fluctuations.

Name: Remote Sample Time
Help: This cut-off voltage will override compressor minimum run time."

Name: Remote Display Locktime
Help: High voltage limit. If the voltage exceeds this limit, the compressor will turn off and is not allowed to start until the line voltage goes below this limit or minimum compressor stop time.

Name: Defrost temperature
Help:
"
"
"
This parameter enhaces the relay life and also avoid relay sparks during relay on and off.This parameter is normally set to 0, which means, that the relay will be switched on and off when the line-voltage crosses zero. Hovewer, if you exactly know the power-factor of your load, you can adjust the switching time to compensate for that.

Name: Condenser temperature
Help: If set, the display will show the temperature in Fahrenheit."

Name: User set
Help: If set, the display will show the temperature with one decimal point.

Name: Voltage
Help: If set, the display will not change value during defrost. The lock time is specified by Remote display Locktime"."

Name: Cutin Cpr
Help: Similar to RLD except that display will show set point value rather than display being locked as DEF"."

Name: Cutout Cpr
Help: If set, you can set the thermostat in stop-position by pressing the two buttons simultaneously for more than 5 seconds. Stop will then be indicated by 3 dashes at the display.

Name: Alarm high temp
Help: This parameter can be used to calibrate for sensor tolerances. It cancels the deviation caused by long lengths of sensor cable.

Name: Alarm low temp
Help: This parameter is used to compensate for bad sensor placement, to minimize the influence of the ambient temperature to the sensor.

Name: Compressor
Help: if RST parameter is set to zero, the temperature would be displayed immediately as it is read from the sensor.  If set to any other value for example 10, ETP R1 would sample the temperature every ten seconds and moving average of 20 samples would be calculated. So if there is a temperature change, the ETPR1 would take 20 multiplied by 10 seconds i.e., 200 Secs(Max) to reach the exact temperature.

Name: Fan
Help: To avoid temperature fluctuations to be visible to the user, you can lock the display to show the temperature before a defrost was started. Or you can let the display show the setpoint. This parameter specifies how long time, it should be locked.

Name: Panel Spindle Selection
Enum: 0:Panel,1:Panel+Spindle with Stop Function,2:Panel + Spindle without stop function
